episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Jessimae Peluso
episodes.summary: Comedian Jessimae Peluso talks to Dom about accents, bowel movements, growing up, fetishes, relationships, and celebrities including Daniel Tosh and Bruce Willis.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Johnny Sanchez Returns
episodes.summary: Actor, writer and comedian Johnny Sanchez returns to the show to talk to Dom about breakdancing, the confederate flag controversy, and Bob Saget on Full House Vs. Bob Saget in real life.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Lowell Sanders
episodes.summary: Actor and comedian Lowell Sanders stops by the show to talk to Dom about rookie strip club mistakes, losing Star Search to a puppet, and their best drug stories.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Steve Byrne
episodes.summary: Writer, actor and comedian Steve Byrne stops by the show to talk to Dom about why stand up comedy is better now than ever, their favorite stand up clubs, and picking up chicks at the Grove after they get out of a taping of The Price Is Right.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Jeremy Hotz Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and writer Jeremy Hotz returns to the show to talk to Dom about the difference between movie fighting and real fighting, their best Siri stories, and how comedy movies don't get any respect.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Adam Ray Returns
episodes.summary: Actor, writer, and comedian Adam Ray returns to the show to talk to Dom about his podcast "About Last Night" with Brad Williams, doing voice-overs for Bruce Willis, and meeting Paul McCartney at the Improv.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Billy Gardell
episodes.summary: Actor, host and comedian Billy Gardell drops by the show to talk to Dom about Mike and Molly, getting kicked off a boat for being drunk and yelling at the captain, and having dinner with Bruce Springsteen.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Michael Patrick King
episodes.summary: Writer, Director and Producer, Michael Patrick King drops by the show to talk to Dom about Murphy Brown, improv Vs stand-up, and being bad Catholics.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Rick Glassman Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, writer, and actor Rick Glassman returns to the show to talk to Dom about NBC's Undateable, who would win in a fight, and dunking to the point of arthritis.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Brian Redban Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, Director and Producer Brian Redban returns to the show to talk to Dom about Hookers, Comedy Drama, and stealing other comedians' essence.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Ahmed Ahmed Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and director Ahmed Ahmed returns to the show to talk to Dom about Bill Cosby, being on TMZ, and having the same name as a most wanted terrorist.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Dov Davidoff Part 5
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and writer Dov Davidoff returns to the show to talk to Dom about taking pills and passing out on stage, New York City Vs. Los Angeles, and crazy-ex girl friend stories.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Tom Dreesen Part 3
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and philanthropist Tom Dreesen returns to the show to talk to Dom about touring with Frank Sinatra, the problems with AA, and dealing with those guys back home who never left the neighborhood.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Kirk Fox
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and writer Kirk Fox stops by the show to talk to Dom about getting Tinnitus from his show "The Test," playing Tennis with Dr. Phil, and being with a girl that's too hot to bring around.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Andrew Santino Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor and writer Andrew Santino returns to the show to talk to Dom about their alcoholism, YouTube haters, and shooting hoops with George Clooney.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Michael Kosta
episodes.summary: Comedian, writer, and pro-athlete Michael Kosta stops by the show to talk to Dom about tennis, bad birthdays, and how a diminishing libido can greatly increase your productivity.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Darren Carter Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and party-starter Darren Carter stops by the show to talk to Dom about rap lyrics, blue-collar vs. redneck, and hanging out with the New Kids on the Block.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Al Madrigal
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor and writer Al Madrigal stops by the show to talk to Dom about getting on The Daily Show, setting a good example for kids, and how to fire people.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Dave Attell Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, writer and actor Dave Attell stops by the show to talk to Dom about Catholic guilt, the difficulties of working clean, and why hotel porn doesn't do the job.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Andy Kindler Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor and voice artist Andy Kindler stops by the show to talk to Dom about about Woody Allen movies, Jay Leno's closet full of Doritos, and when "jew" was a punchline.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Dan Ahdoot
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor and writer Dan Ahdoot stops by the show to talk to Dom about about ISIS, Falafel Phil, and the dangers of dating comedians.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Tom Wilson
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor and artist Tom Wilson stops by the show to talk to Dom about bullies, Back to the Future, and how dangerous the Comedy Store was in the 80's.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Flip Schultz
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and writer Flip Schultz drops by the show to chat with Dom about bombing, clowns, and "borrowing" jokes from Sam Kinison.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Grant Cotter
episodes.summary: Comedian, writer, and prankster Grant Cotter drops by the show to chat with Dom about cocky comedians, skanky strippers, and making girls cry.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Jake Johannsen
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and writer Jake Johannsen drops by the show to chat with Dom about Robin Williams, the NSA, and offending hookers with golf-claps.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Tom Papa Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and writer Tom Papa makes a return visit to chat with Dom about drinking and drugging, not apologizing for your comedy, and his fall-back plans for when he crashes and burns.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Bill Dawes Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian and actor Bill Dawes returns to the show to tell Dom about getting in fights, being on Broadway, and getting married to please your mother.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Kira Soltanovich Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor and writer Kira Soltanovich makes a return visit to chat with Dom about not knowing how to be Jewish, her top 3 favorite comedians, and mentally quitting comedy a couple times a week.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: John Henson Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, TV host, and actor John Henson makes a return visit to chat with Dom about Wipeout, giving people the "full court press", and the horrors of discovering the porn you're watching was filmed in your house!

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Justin Martindale
episodes.summary: Comedian and DeathSquad podcaster Justin Martindale drops by the show to chat with Dom about the Sunset Strip in the 80s, how easy it is to get drunk when you're constantly offered free drinks, and their favorite curse words.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Todd Glass Returns!
episodes.summary: Comedian and podcaster Todd Glass makes a return visit to chat with Dom about coming up in Philly together, the joy of busting balls, and the low-stakes curse of wishing fatigue upon someone.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Erin Foley
episodes.summary: Actress, comedian, and writer Erin Foley drops by the show to talk with Dom about messed up intros, coming out of the closet, and Derek Jeter's retirement.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Bill Burr - Part 3
episodes.summary: Comedian and actor Bill Burr makes his hat trick appearance! He and Dom survey The Beatles' greatest hits, talk sports up and down, and get into their favorite hacky jokes.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Elon Gold
episodes.summary: Comedian, actor, and writer Elon Gold drops by the show to pay tribute to Joan Rivers, show off some impressions, and explore a recent unfortunate hate incident.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: John Heffron
episodes.summary: Comedian John Heffron drops by the show to chat with Dom about their favorite dirty word, social media, and life on the road.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Rick Overton Returns
episodes.summary: Comedian, writer, and actor Rick Overton makes a return visit to pay tribute with Dom to the legendary Robin Williams.

episodes.seriesTitle: Dom Irrera Live from the Laugh Factory
episodes.title: Gerry Bednob
episodes.summary: Actor and comedian Gerry Bednob drops by the show to chat with Dom about their roots, why it's dumb to say you're "crushing it", and Robin Williams.
